2:29:14 Some lore from a boring nerd for Watson:

- The planet is always the same, Hoxxes 4. However, it has zones (biomes) with different weather, map features and sometimes different enemies. For example, electricity crystals appear only in Crystalline Caverns, while green glowing radioactive crystals appear only in the Radioactive Zone (where you are right now).
- Who is Karl is an interesting and old question. There isn't much info on him, but the word is, he was a legendary miner who disappeared on Hoxxes 4. Some consider him dead, but many believe he's still alive somewhere below, because he's a Doom Slayer of DRG. Bugs fear him, dwarves want to be like him.
- Players often argue which class is best in DRG, but the truth is, each one does something that the others cannot. When they work as a team, they can do wonders. For example, Scout can get everywhere with his hook but he can't mine while hanging on it. So he actually badly need Engie's platforms. Engie, on the other hand, is a walking powerhouse and good point defense guy, but he is limited if he can't see things - and Scout's big flares can help him avoid deep pits and plan turret positions for best lines of fire.
Playing as two scouts (or even a full team of four scouts) may be fun, but is actually more difficult because they will all have the same weakness. It's absolutely okay to focus on one class you like the most.
- Engineer's turrets can't walk. But in some missions you can encounter other machines that can walk or even fly - and with some luck befriend them ;)
- DRG universe has other species, like elves, but so far they don't appear in the game.
